===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|closen||to close, enclose|lang=enm}}, from {{term|clos||pos=adjective|close, shut up, confined, secret|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|fro}} {{term|clos||close, confined|pos=adjective|lang=fro}}, from {{etyl|la}} {{term|clausus||shut up|pos=past participle|lang=la}}, from {{term|claudere||to bar, block, close, enclose, bring an end to, confine|lang=la}}, from {{proto|Indo-European|klāw-|key, hook, nail|lang=en}}, related to {{etyl|la|-}} {{term|clavis|clāvis|key, deadbolt, bar|lang=la}}, {{term|clavus|clāvus|nail, peg|lang=la}}, {{term|claustrum||bar, bolt, barrier|lang=la}}, {{term|claustra||dam, wall, barricade, stronghold|lang=la}}. Cognate with {{etyl|grc|-}} {{term|κλείς||bar, bolt, key|lang=grc}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|schließen||to close, conclude, lock|lang=de}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|sluiten||to close, conclude, lock|lang=nl}}. Replaced {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|lucan|lūcan|to close, lock, enclose|lang=ang}} and {{term|clysan|clȳsan|sc=Latinx|to close, shut|lang=ang}}.

